+## 1. Deep analysis â€” bugs, risks, gaps, improvements found in the sources
+
+Findings from auditing the prototype (`project/*.jsx`), the article, and the
+AskMyDocs code. These become guardrails or backlog items in the tasks below.
+
+### A. Prototype bugs / weaknesses to FIX when porting
+1. **`RJsonPath` renderer is a stub** (`cells.jsx`): it ignores the detected type and always delegates to `RPercentage`. Real impl must auto-detect (number/money/date/text) and render accordingly with a `$` sigil. â†’ M4.
+2. **Citation numbering is global & recomputed every render** (`grid.jsx` `citCounter`): O(rowsÃ—cols) each paint, and numbers reshuffle on data change. Make it stable per cell. â†’ M4.
+3. **`generateFakeValue` desyncs from real LLM shape**: AI-Suggest fake cells use `{v: ...}` while LLM path uses `{value, flag, citation}`. Normalize on one DTO. â†’ M2/M5.
+4. **No enum palette persistence**: `REnum` falls back to a hash hue; `enum_values_palette` is referenced but never populated. Decide: deterministic hash is fine for demo; document it. â†’ M4.
+5. **Percentage parsing is fragile** (`RPercentage`): mixes `+18%` / `-42%` / bare numbers; negative/positive coloring relies on string prefix. Centralize parsing + guard `NaN` (lesson from reference repo: never let `NaN` reach color logic). â†’ M4.
+6. **`resolveJsonPath` "cheats"** in the demo (returns fallback). Real json_path must resolve against the row JSON (the AskMyDocs `descend()`/`parseJsonPath()` algorithm handles `$.a.b`, `a.b`, `$['a']['b']`). â†’ M2.
+7. **No cancellation safety on preset switch mid-run**: switching preset while `running` can patch stale cells into the new preset. Guard with a run token / abort. â†’ M4.
+8. **Mock stagger uses many `setTimeout`s** â€” fine for prototype, but the real SSE consumer must use a single EventSource and atomic `updateCells`. â†’ M4.
+9. **DOM grid won't scale**: prototype renders all rows as divs. Article's own thesis: use canvas (Glide) for 100k rows. We adopt Glide from the start. â†’ M4.
+
+### B. Article claims that need a demo-appropriate simplification
+10. Article uses Redis pub/sub + Horizon + KB chunks + reranker confidence. For the demo: synchronous SSE, row-as-context, and a deterministic **FlagClassifier** (green/yellow/red/grey) derived from the LLM's own flag + simple heuristics (mock supplies the flag). â†’ M2.
+11. `confidence_score` from a reranker doesn't exist here â†’ derive a pseudo-confidence from flag (greenâ‰ˆ0.9, yellowâ‰ˆ0.65, greyâ‰ˆ0.4, redâ‰ˆ0.2) so the UI tint still works. Document as demo-only. â†’ M2.
+12. Batched JSON-lines call is kept (real cost win + matches AskMyDocs). One LLM call per row, one JSON object per column line. â†’ M2.
+
+### C. SDK / integration facts to respect (from AskMyDocs)
+13. `laravel/ai` real surface: `Laravel\Ai\AnonymousAgent`, `Laravel\Ai\Messages\{UserMessage,AssistantMessage}`, `Laravel\Ai\Gateway\TextGenerationOptions::forAgent()`, response `Laravel\Ai\Responses\AgentResponse` with `->text`, `->usage->{promptTokens,completionTokens}`, `->meta->model`, `->steps->last()?->finishReason`.
+14. **`max_tokens`/`temperature` are silently dropped** unless the agent exposes `maxTokens()`/`temperature()` (AskMyDocs created `RegoloAnonymousAgent` to fix this). We must verify our agent forwards options; add a unit test asserting options reach the wire (or via the provider config). â†’ M2 + LESSON.
+15. Persist cells via an **atomic DB upsert** keyed by `(review_id, row_id, column_index)`, then re-`first()` â€” Eloquent `updateOrCreate` is not atomic (race under concurrency). â†’ M2.
+16. **Never surface raw provider exception messages** in API responses (may leak hostnames/keys). Log full, return a generic "provider error" cell. â†’ M2 + security rule.
+17. JSON-encode cell content with `JSON_THROW_ON_ERROR | JSON_INVALID_UTF8_SUBSTITUTE`; on failure degrade to a red cell. â†’ M2.
+18. R14 (refusal): a row/column with no usable context returns `flag:red, summary:null` â€” never an empty 200. â†’ M2.
+
+### D. Feature gaps in the prototype worth adding for a convincing demo
+19. **Citation popover side-panel** (article Â§13): click a cell â†’ right side-panel showing value, flag, reasoning, model, tokens, citation text, prompt used, actions (Regenerate / Copy). Demo-grade (no real source-doc viewer). â†’ M5 (stretch; ship at least value+reasoning+citation+regenerate).
+20. **Bulk regenerate**: Glide native multi-select â†’ toolbar "Regenerate selected". â†’ M5.
+21. **Skeleton/progress**: per-cell `Loading` kind + top progress bar `done/total` (prototype has both). â†’ M4.
+22. **Export XLSX** is a stub alert in the prototype â€” keep a stub button (out of scope), or a trivial CSV download. Decide CSV download (cheap, real). â†’ M6.
+23. **16-format showcase preset** must render every renderer once â€” great Playwright assertion target. â†’ M6.
+
+### E. Cross-cutting guardrails (from reference repo LESSON.md)
+- CSV/any export must neutralize spreadsheet formulas (`=,+,-,@`).
+- Source/`url` cells: restrict to `http:`/`https:` before any `window.open`.
+- Playwright on Windows: Herd PHP, exact label selectors, clean up created rows in `finally`, don't assume globally-unique rows under parallel projects.
+- Vitest in CI: `pool: 'threads'`, set `LARAVEL_BYPASS_ENV_CHECK=1`, validate lockfile with `npx npm@10 ci --dry-run`.
+- Controllers must not call `env()`; read `config()`.
